Package: JeromePlumierCountAllMissingByGroup
Type: Package
Title: Count Missing Values For All Columns By Group
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Jérôme", "Plumier", email = "jplumier@student.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This R package contains the function count_all_missing_by_group 
  that, given a data frame data and a column group, creates a new data frame
  with one row per level of group. The first column of the output data
  frame contains the levels of group, and the rest of the columns
  contain the number of missing values for all columns in data except group.
